    <statement>
        
                <p>
                    The board of trustees at the Da Vinci Institute consists of 14 people. During the spring, a delegation of 6 trustees will be assigned to an outreach committee. How many such delegations are possible?
                </p>
        
        
        <p>

        </p>
        <p>
        Show all of your steps, specify which formula you used, and state why you used it.
        </p>
    </statement>
    <answer>
        <p> We are selecting 6 from a total of 14 possibilities (without repeats), and the order of the selections does not matter. There are <m>_{14}C_{6}</m> <m> = 3003</m> possibilities.</p>
    </answer>
</exercise>
